description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Flexible base within one of GMAST’s team bases across the Midlands - to be agreed with the successful candidate)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for an enthusiastic individual to join the General Medical Advice and Support Team (GMAST) in the Midlands region as an admin assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have previous administrative experience, preferably within an NHS setting. Good written and verbal communication skills are essential together with highly effective organisational and planning skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Office packages is essential for this post, along with a strong commitment to teamwork and the flexibility to provide cross cover when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide general administration duties, which may include but is not limited to; the preparation of agendas and meeting notes; raising purchase orders; providing general administrative support including handling correspondence, printing and collation of papers, taking responsibility for the scheduling and co-ordination of meetings, updating various worksheets/trackers, management of the generic email inbox and dealing with any queries relating to purchase orders on behalf of the Midland’s team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post requires excellent communication and organisational skills and for the successful candidate to work effectively in a close team setting, having the ability to plan and prioritise their own workload and work flexibly in response to service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matthew Grubb, Contracts Officer; matthew.grubb@nhs.net available Monday - Friday between 10:00 - 16:00&lt;/p&gt;
